"title": "5274: credit",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5274",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Money or goods lent under pledge of repayment (with or without interest). In the spiritual sense, Jesus Christ's righteousness is credited to believers.</p>\n<h2>Credit in Israel: charitable, not commercial</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:19-Deut23:20\">DEU 23:19–23:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:25\">EXO 22:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:5\">PSA 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:7\">EZK 18:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:16-Ezek18:17\">EZK 18:16–18:17</a></p>\n<h2>The pledge (security):  laws protecting the borrower</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:10-Deut24:13\">DEU 24:10–24:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:26-Exod22:27\">EXO 22:26–22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:40\">LEV 25:39–25:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:42\">LEV 25:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:6\">DEU 24:6</a></p>\n<h2>Standing security for another may be hazardous</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:26-Prov22:27\">PRO 22:26–22:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:1-Prov6:5\">PRO 6:1–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:15\">PRO 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:18\">PRO 17:18</a> <em>The binding nature of the commitment cautions against a hasty and unwise engagement.</em></p>\n<h2>Violations of Israel's ``credit controls'' roundly condemned</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:1-Neh5:12\">NEH 5:1–5:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:6\">JOB 22:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:3\">JOB 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:9\">JOB 24:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:12\">EZK 18:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:8\">AMO 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>The credit system not condemned by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:27\">MAT 25:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:23\">LUK 19:23</a></p>\n<h2>Christians to view this subject in the light of God's grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:34-Luke6:35\">LUK 6:34–6:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:23-Matt18:27\">MAT 18:23–18:27</a> <em>God is a model creditor.</em></p>\n<h2>Creditors demanding a pledge to assure repayment</h2>\n<h3>A personal effect</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:6\">DEU 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:10-Deut24:13\">DEU 24:10–24:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:3\">JOB 24:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:26-Prov22:27\">PRO 22:26–22:27</a></p>\n<h3>Mortgage of property</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:3\">NEH 5:3</a></p>\n<h3>The surety of a guarantor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:1-Prov6:5\">PRO 6:1–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:15\">PRO 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:18\">PRO 17:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:26\">PRO 22:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:13\">PRO 27:13</a></p>\n<h2>Creditors exacting repayments cruelly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:1\">2KI 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:6\">JOB 22:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:3\">JOB 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:9\">JOB 24:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:11\">PSA 109:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:1\">ISA 50:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:12-Ezek18:13\">EZK 18:12–18:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:12\">EZK 22:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6\">AMO 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:8\">AMO 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25-Matt5:26\">MAT 5:25–5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:25-Matt18:26\">MAT 18:25–18:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:34\">MAT 18:34</a></p>\n<h2>Creditors to be considerate in their demands</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:6\">DEU 24:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:26-Exod22:27\">EXO 22:26–22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:35-Lev25:43\">LEV 25:35–25:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:10-Deut24:13\">DEU 24:10–24:13</a></p>\n<h2>Creditors perhaps remitting the debt entirely</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:27\">MAT 18:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:10-Neh5:12\">NEH 5:10–5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12\">MAT 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:41-Luke7:43\">LUK 7:41–7:43</a></p>\n<h2>Under Mosaic law creditors to cancel debts eventually</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:1-Deut15:3\">DEU 15:1–15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:10\">DEU 31:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:31\">NEH 10:31</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual aspects of credit</h2>\n<h3>Faith credited as righteousness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:1-Rom4:11\">ROM 4:1–4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:2\">PSA 32:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:31\">PSA 106:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:20\">EZK 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:22-Rom4:24\">ROM 4:22–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:23\">JAS 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's righteousness credited to believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:22\">ROM 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:9\">PHP 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Moral aspects of credit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:17\">PHP 4:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:40-Matt10:42\">MAT 10:40–10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34-Matt25:36\">MAT 25:34–25:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:32-Luke6:35\">LUK 6:32–6:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:7-Eph6:8\">EPH 6:7–6:8</a> <em>Good deeds will be remembered and rewarded in heaven.</em></p>",
